# 2024-12-17 15:52:17.714142
+this is the feedback, fix it and remove all references pump.fun with appropriate replacent: There is a significant technical inaccuracy regarding the use of Solidity on Solana. Solana smart contracts are typically written in Rust or C/C++ and compiled to run on the Solana runtime; they are not deployed using Solidity. This should be corrected to ensure technical credibility. Additionally, minor points include introducing “MainstreamCoin” without prior explanation, referencing the “pump.fun” platform without context, and ensuring that all mentioned concepts are clearly explained and consistent.
+
+Detailed Analysis:
+
+Technical Stack Inconsistency (Solana and Solidity):
+
+The document mentions that smart contracts for the MainstreamToken (MT) will be written in Solidity and deployed on Solana. Solana’s architecture is distinct from EVM-compatible chains, and it does not use Solidity natively. Developers typically write Solana programs in Rust or C, and they are compiled to the Solana bytecode format.
+To maintain technical rigor, replace any mention of Solidity with Rust or clarify if an EVM bridge is being used. If the project intends to remain Solana-native, it must reflect Solana’s development ecosystem accurately.
+Introduction of Concepts Without Background:
+
