# 2024-12-19 13:29:23.388927
+check for errors and fix it : TutorialHow to Buy Mainstream Tokens (MT)
+How to Buy Mainstream Tokens (MT)
+This tutorial explains how to acquire Mainstream Tokens (MT) through various methods.
+
+Prerequisites
+Before buying MT tokens, you'll need:
+
+A Solana wallet (like Phantom or Solflare)
+Some SOL tokens for transaction fees
+Access to a supported exchange
+Buying Steps
+1. Set Up Your Wallet
+Install a Solana wallet extension
+Create a new wallet or import existing
+Securely store your recovery phrase
+Add some SOL for fees
+2. Find MT Token Markets
+MT tokens are available on:
+
+Decentralized exchanges (DEX)
+Automated market makers (AMM)
+Direct purchase platforms
+3. Connect Your Wallet
+Visit the exchange website
+Click "Connect Wallet"
+Select your wallet
+Approve the connection
+4. Make Your Purchase
+Find the MT/SOL trading pair
+Enter the amount to buy
+Review the transaction details
+Confirm the purchase
+Safety Tips
+Always verify contract addresses
+Start with small test transactions
+Keep your wallet secure
+Don't share private keys
+Support
+For help with purchases, join our Telegram community.
+sidebar_position: 4
+How to Buy Mainstream Tokens (MT)
+This tutorial will guide you through the process of purchasing Mainstream Tokens (MT) to support the project.
+
+Understanding MT
+Mainstream Token (MT) is a digital asset on the Solana blockchain. It is used within the Mainstream ecosystem for various purposes, including accessing licensed content and participating in community governance.
+
+Purchasing MT Tokens
+Initial Distribution
+The initial distribution of MT tokens was facilitated through a bonding curve mechanism on a decentralized platform. This mechanism ensures transparent price discovery and initial liquidity generation.
+
+Current Methods
+Currently, MT tokens can be purchased on decentralized exchanges (DEX) on the Solana blockchain.
+
+Step-by-Step Guide
+Set Up a Solana Wallet:
+
+If you don't have one, create a Solana wallet using a trusted provider like Phantom, Solflare, or similar.
+Make sure to securely store your seed phrase or private key.
+Acquire SOL:
+
+You will need some SOL (Solana's native token) to pay for transaction fees.
+Purchase SOL from a centralized exchange (CEX) like Coinbase, Binance, or Kraken, and transfer it to your Solana wallet.
+Connect to a DEX:
+
+Visit a Solana-based decentralized exchange (DEX) such as Raydium, Orca, or Jupiter.
+Connect your Solana wallet to the DEX.
+Find the MT Trading Pair:
+
+Search for the MT token using its contract address or ticker symbol.
+Make sure you are using the correct contract address to avoid purchasing fake tokens.
+The official contract address will be available on the project's website and official communication channels.
+Swap SOL for MT:
+
+Enter the amount of SOL you want to swap for MT.
+Review the transaction details, including the price and fees.
+Confirm the swap transaction in your wallet.
+Verify the Transaction:
+
+Once the transaction is confirmed, verify that the MT tokens are in your Solana wallet.
+Important Considerations
+Slippage: Be aware of slippage, which is the difference between the expected price and the actual price you receive due to market volatility.
+Transaction Fees: Solana transactions have small fees, so make sure you have enough SOL to cover them.
+Security: Always use trusted platforms and double-check the contract address before making any purchases.
+Volatility: The price of MT tokens can be volatile, so be prepared for potential price fluctuations.
+DYOR: Always Do Your Own Research before investing in any cryptocurrency.
+Community Support
+By purchasing MT tokens, you are supporting the MainstreamToken project and its community. Your participation helps to further develop the ecosystem and its goals.
+
+This tutorial provides a basic overview of how to purchase MT tokens. For more detailed information, please refer to the project's website and official communication channels.

# 2024-12-19 13:30:03.827441
+find errors and fix it  : Tutorialencoder-decoder
+encoder-decoder
+sidebar_position: 3
+Using the MTL Encoder and Decoder
+This tutorial will guide you through using the MTL Encoder and Decoder apps to create and understand Mainstream Token Licenses (MTL).
+
+MTL Encoder
+The MTL Encoder app allows you to create custom MTL strings by specifying various parameters.
+
+Accessing the Encoder
+Navigate to the "Apps" menu in the navigation bar.
+Select "MTL Generator" from the dropdown menu.
+Using the Encoder
+License Type: Select one or more license types (Personal, Commercial, Non-Profit, Derivative).
+Token Amount: Enter the number of Mainstream Tokens (MT) required for the license.
+Fee: Enter the percentage fee for revenue sharing (0-100).
+Fee Collection Wallet: Enter the Solana wallet address that will receive the fees.
+Revenue Splits: Define how the revenue will be split between different wallets.
+Duration: Specify how long the license will be valid for.
+Revenue Cap: Set the maximum revenue allowed under this license.
+Revenue Min: Set the minimum revenue required to maintain this license.
+Revenue Exact: Set the exact revenue amount required for this license.
+Revenue Max: Set the maximum revenue threshold that must not be exceeded.
+Region: Specify geographic regions where the license is valid.
+Usage: Specify usage types allowed (e.g., web, mobile, games).
+Addendum: Add additional license terms or references.
+Click "Generate License String" to create the MTL string.
+Click "Copy" to copy the generated license string to your clipboard.
+MTL Decoder
+The MTL Decoder app allows you to decode an existing MTL string to understand its parameters.
+
+Accessing the Decoder
+Navigate to the "Apps" menu in the navigation bar.
+Select "MTL Decoder" from the dropdown menu.
+Using the Decoder
+License String: Paste the MTL string you want to decode into the text area.
+Click "Decode License" to view the decoded parameters.
+Review the decoded information, including license types, token amount, fee, splits, duration, revenue conditions, region, usage, and addendum.
+Example
+Let's say you want to create a license for commercial use, requiring 1000 MT tokens, with a 5% fee, a 30% split to the protocol, 40% to the creator, and 30% to a smart contract, valid for 1 year, with a revenue cap of $1 million, for use in the US, on the web, with a CC-BY license.
+
+Using the MTL Encoder, you would:
+
+Select "Commercial Use".
+Enter "1000" for the token amount.
+Enter "5" for the fee.
+Enter the fee collection wallet.
+Add the revenue splits.
+Enter "1" for the duration value and select "Y" for years.
+Enter "1000000" for the revenue cap.
+Enter "US" for the region.
+Enter "W" for the usage.
+Enter "LICENSE:CC-BY" for the addendum.
+Click "Generate License String".
+The generated MTL string would be:
+
+MTLv1-C/1000-5:30:40:30;+1Y<1000000[US]{W}~LICENSE:CC-BY
+
+You can then use the MTL Decoder to verify the parameters of this license string.
+
+This tutorial provides a basic overview of how to use the MTL Encoder and Decoder apps. For more detailed information, please refer to the specific sections on parameters, verification, and payment.
+
+

